ANTHRAX - ARMENIA (08): INCREASED HUMAN CASES
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 4 Dec 2012
Source: Vestnik/News Armenia [edited]
http://vestnikkavkaza.net/news/society/34482.html


Anthrax outbreak in Armenia
---------------------------
A total of 55 cases with anthrax symptoms have been registered in Armenia. 10 of them have already been confirmed.

In October [2012], 21 people with anthrax symptoms were hospitalized in the Gegarkunik Region of Armenia. A local resident of Ushi in the Aragots Region was hospitalized with anthrax in early November. Animals with anthrax were registered in the Tavush and Armavir Regions.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is a terse report. To date we have a single OIE report of 2 outbreaks in cattle in Gegarkunik region, plus side comments of outbreaks in Tavush and Armavir regions, whereas there are now multiple human cases in Gegarkunik, Aragots, and Kotayk regions. Contaminated meat can be marketed some distance from where the sick animal was butchered. And in this way one cow can infect 10, 20, 30 humans.

For a map of Armenia go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/armenia_rel_2002.jpg. The named regions are all in central Armenia. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1HT_.]
